A middle-aged man, Victor Ibemesim has been traumatized over the sudden disappearance of his 13-year old ward in Nkpor in Idemili North Local Government Area of Anambra State. The victim, Isaac Mezie Nwanegbo, a native of Anam in Anambra West Local Government Area of the state was last seen wearing a school uniform. The Nation gathered that efforts to trace Isaac’s whereabouts had been unsuccessful. Police spokesperson, Haruna Mohammed confirmed the incident in a statement. He said, “This is to inform the general public that one Isaac Mezie Nwanegbo ‘m’ aged 13years of No.15 Offor street Nkpor in Idemili North LGA of Anambra State was reported missing by his guardian one Mr. Victor Ibemesim ‘m’ of the same address. “The missing child who hails from Anam in Anambra West LGA of Anambra is four feet tall, dark in complexion, speaks Igbo and English languages fluently and with no tribal mark. “The boy was last seen wearing a school uniform white and blue and all efforts to trace his whereabouts proved abortive. “Anyone with useful information about the Child’s whereabouts should report at Ogidi Divisional Police Station or contact PPRO Anambra State Police Command through GSM no 08060970639.”